      <section eId="sec_250_40">
        <num>250.40</num>
        <heading>Unlawful surveillance; definitions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_250_40__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>disseminate, as defined in subdivision five\nof this section, with the intent that such image or images be\ndisseminated to ten or more persons; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250_40__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>disseminate with the intent\nthat such images be sold by another person; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250_40__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>post, present,\ndisplay, exhibit, circulate, advertise or allows access, electronically\nor otherwise, so as to make an image or images available to the public;\nor</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250_40__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>disseminate with the intent that an image or images be posted,\npresented, displayed, exhibited, circulated, advertised or made\naccessible, electronically or otherwise and to make such image or images\navailable to the public.\n  7. "Sell" means to disseminate to another person, as defined in\nsubdivision five of this section, or to publish, as defined in\nsubdivision six of this section, in exchange for something of value.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
